He's in the federal
psych hospital.

26:11.170 --> 26:12.728
And this is
a life-or-death situation.

26:12.800 --> 26:14.233
I think they're gonna
let me talk to him.

26:14.300 --> 26:16.063
Now, there's a phone call
I'd like to be on.

26:16.140 --> 26:19.507
I'll get Navabi to go out
to the RV parking lot...
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

26:19.570 --> 26:21.834
I mean, y-you're welcome
to listen in if you want,

26:21.910 --> 26:24.845
but, with Reddington,
you catch more flies
with honey,

26:24.910 --> 26:27.470
and you are definitely
more sour than sweet.

26:27.550 --> 26:29.643
(KEYS JINGLING)

26:29.720 --> 26:31.142
How do you do it?

26:31.220 --> 26:32.915
What?
Put up with him.

26:32.990 --> 26:35.117
I can't stand
how much he hides from us,

26:35.190 --> 26:36.782
and I'm not even his kid.

26:36.860 --> 26:38.987
I don't know
how you deal with it.
It's not easy.

26:39.060 --> 26:40.721
You make it look like it is.
(SCOFFS)

26:40.800 --> 26:43.325
(CELLPHONE DIALING)
I'll let you know
what I find out.

26:43.400 --> 26:45.595
I'll do the same.

26:45.670 --> 26:47.490
(DOOR CLOSES)
(LINE RINGING)

26:47.570 --> 26:49.435
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

27:11.230 --> 27:14.552
Cameron Morella! FBI!
Open the door.

27:15.730 --> 27:17.391
Mr. Morella, open the door,

27:17.460 --> 27:20.839
_ or a tactical team
Will storm your vehicle!

27:20.900 --> 27:23.232
Hands where I can see them.

27:23.300 --> 27:26.007
Where's the cavalry?
In my hand. Now back up.

27:33.280 --> 27:35.214
Well, I guess there
won't be much more from him,

27:35.280 --> 27:37.783
now, will there?
That's the idea.

27:39.790 --> 27:41.257
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

27:44.130 --> 27:45.154
Atticus.

27:45.230 --> 27:46.925
Atticus.

27:46.990 --> 27:48.389
We don't have much time.

27:48.460 --> 27:50.018
Hey.

27:50.100 --> 27:51.727
Hey.

27:51.800 --> 27:54.166
Your friend has a job.

27:54.240 --> 27:55.992
It's an assassination.

27:56.070 --> 27:57.901
Look at me.

27:57.970 --> 28:00.438
He knows the FBI
is looking for him,

28:00.510 --> 28:04.048
so it has to be
done quietly.

28:04.110 --> 28:05.941
I'd like to fly.

28:06.010 --> 28:07.841
Hey, hey. Hey.

28:10.350 --> 28:12.341
Your friend,
who would he turn to,

28:12.420 --> 28:16.550
to get a job done
as quietly as possible?

28:16.620 --> 28:20.624
Atticus,
who would he turn to?

28:20.690 --> 28:24.365
General...Shiro...

28:24.430 --> 28:26.227
Ge... General...
(STAMMERING) Who's that?

28:26.300 --> 28:28.939
I-I don't...
General Shiro?

28:29.000 --> 28:31.036
Hey, where
can I find him?

28:31.110 --> 28:33.704
Would you like to fly?

28:33.780 --> 28:35.099
Oh.

28:35.180 --> 28:36.431
I would.

28:44.620 --> 28:47.544
I know who you are,
Mr. Morella.

28:47.620 --> 28:49.485
I know you murdered
Kelly Carter

28:49.560 --> 28:51.289
to prevent her
from telling a grand jury

28:51.360 --> 28:53.419
_that she saw
Digby Tamerlane

28:53.490 --> 28:56.789
trying to hide the body
of a young girl he killed

28:56.860 --> 28:58.794
in a hit-and-run.

28:58.870 --> 29:00.064
I don't know
what you're talking about.

29:00.130 --> 29:02.667
I also know who you were,

29:02.740 --> 29:04.628
Dr. Klepper.

29:06.070 --> 29:07.606
I don't know that name.

29:07.670 --> 29:08.830
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

29:13.750 --> 29:15.377
(DOOR CREAKS)

29:18.920 --> 29:20.319
Is that him?
(DOOR CLOSES)

29:20.390 --> 29:22.153
LIZ: He says no.

29:22.220 --> 29:24.586
But I think
this should change his mind.

29:31.200 --> 29:33.794
Look familiar?

29:33.870 --> 29:35.337
It should.
It's a picture of you

29:35.400 --> 29:36.992
in Dr. Hans Koehler's
medical file,

29:37.070 --> 29:39.265
complete with a list
of every time he chiseled you

29:39.340 --> 29:40.534
or injected you,

29:40.610 --> 29:42.168
shaved you down
or puffed you up.

29:42.240 --> 29:43.673
I don't recognize
this person.

29:43.740 --> 29:45.674
Well, Koehler
did a remarkable job

29:45.750 --> 29:48.719
of changing
your appearance.

29:48.780 --> 29:52.318
But we both know that
he can't change your DNA.

29:52.390 --> 29:55.450
And that when we do take it,
it's gonna match up to his.

29:55.520 --> 29:56.953
Isn't it, Doctor?

30:01.130 --> 30:02.688
I like to make
calculations.

30:02.760 --> 30:04.864
Like deciding who should live
and who should die?

30:04.930 --> 30:06.693
That's one
calculation, yes.

30:06.770 --> 30:08.169
Have you made it often?

30:08.240 --> 30:09.730
Often enough.

30:09.800 --> 30:11.631
And it's a surprisingly
easy one.

30:11.710 --> 30:14.133
Others are considerably
more difficult.

30:14.210 --> 30:17.304
Like why the FBI sent
only one agent and one...

30:17.380 --> 30:19.871
I'm not sure what.
We know who you were

30:19.950 --> 30:22.646
before Dr. Koehler
changed your identity.

30:22.720 --> 30:26.884
What we want to know is
who Raymond Reddington was.

30:26.950 --> 30:28.679
LIZ: According
to Koehler's records,

30:28.760 --> 30:30.079
you and Reddington
were patients

30:30.160 --> 30:31.889
at approximately
the same time.

30:31.960 --> 30:35.088
And you think, what, we bonded
in post-op? Compared scars?

30:35.160 --> 30:36.752
(CHUCKLES) The whole point
of going to Koehler

30:36.830 --> 30:38.092
was to become anonymous.

30:38.170 --> 30:40.730
I never saw him.
He never saw me.

30:40.800 --> 30:43.098
(CELLPHONE VIBRATING)

30:51.050 --> 30:52.403
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

30:52.480 --> 30:54.345
Whatcha got?
A guy at the RV park

30:54.420 --> 30:56.570
gave us a description
of Klepper's vehicle.

30:56.650 --> 30:58.083
Aram tracked it
to a parking lot

30:58.150 --> 31:00.789
at 3rd and Sycamore.

31:00.850 --> 31:02.408
How far away are you?

31:02.490 --> 31:03.923
About 10 minutes out.

31:03.990 --> 31:05.628
Lemme know what you find
when you get there.

31:05.690 --> 31:07.954
What about Reddington?
Reddington?

31:08.030 --> 31:09.429
Well, did you talk to him?

31:09.500 --> 31:11.889
Oh. Yeah.
He didn't know anything.

31:11.970 --> 31:14.029
For once we know
more than he does.

31:14.100 --> 31:17.228
All right, I'll, uh, call you
when we find something.

31:17.300 --> 31:19.939
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

31:20.010 --> 31:22.205
I have a gun.

31:22.280 --> 31:24.271
In that cupboard.
On the top shelf.

31:31.690 --> 31:34.079
About Reddington...

31:34.160 --> 31:35.752
If you didn't see him,
who did?

31:35.820 --> 31:37.458
A nurse.

31:37.520 --> 31:40.125
She saw all the patients,
before and after.

31:40.190 --> 31:41.748
She could tell you
who Reddington was.

31:41.830 --> 31:43.252
What's her name?

31:43.330 --> 31:45.161
Your colleagues
are on their way.

31:45.230 --> 31:47.266
And for some reason,
you didn't tell them
you were already here.

31:47.330 --> 31:49.298
What is her name?
I don't randomly decide

31:49.370 --> 31:50.769
who's gonna live or die.

31:50.840 --> 31:53.058
I do it based on
whose life has more value.

31:53.140 --> 31:55.108
Take us, for example.

31:55.180 --> 31:57.307
I'm gonna spend the rest
of my life in prison.

31:57.380 --> 31:59.302
You could have a long
and productive career.

31:59.380 --> 32:02.838
By any reasonable standard,
your life has more value,

32:02.920 --> 32:04.285
which is why
you should get my gun.

32:04.350 --> 32:07.808
We need a name.
And I'll give it to you

32:07.890 --> 32:09.755
once I get you to understand
that you have to kill me.

32:09.820 --> 32:12.823
What are you talking about?
I don't know why you want to
know who Reddington was,

32:12.890 --> 32:15.791
but clearly you're willing to
risk a great deal to find out.

32:15.860 --> 32:19.023
Your career, all the good and
productive things you'll do

32:19.100 --> 32:21.034
that makes your life
more valuable than mine,

32:21.100 --> 32:22.636
but it only has that value

32:22.700 --> 32:24.361
if your colleagues
never find out you were here.

32:24.440 --> 32:25.702
And the only way
that's gonna happen

32:25.770 --> 32:27.863
is if I'm dead
when they arrive.

32:27.940 --> 32:31.171
Like I said,
it's a surprisingly
easy calculation.

32:31.250 --> 32:33.468
We're not gonna kill you.

32:33.550 --> 32:35.370
Of course not.

32:35.450 --> 32:37.668
You're gonna
kill yourself.

32:37.750 --> 32:39.388
That's what you do.
You stage killings

32:39.450 --> 32:40.849
and make them
look like accidents.

32:40.920 --> 32:42.979
Or suicides.

32:43.060 --> 32:45.051
My gun.

32:45.130 --> 32:46.381
You don't have
much time.

32:46.460 --> 32:47.688
Either I die here

32:47.760 --> 32:49.853
or I spend my life
behind bars.

32:49.930 --> 32:52.125
In some ways,
it's a mercy killing.

32:57.970 --> 33:00.336
You're not _
actually conSidering...

33:00.410 --> 33:01.934
Wait in the car.

33:02.010 --> 33:03.329
You can't do this.

33:03.410 --> 33:04.741
KLEPPER:
The gun for the name.

33:04.810 --> 33:06.869
If she wants the name,
she has no choice.

33:08.780 --> 33:10.077
Go.

33:13.890 --> 33:15.380
This isn't right.

33:22.860 --> 33:24.691
Marguerite Renard.

33:24.770 --> 33:28.331
Find her, you'll find out
who Reddington was.

33:31.740 --> 33:33.605
It's the ethical thing
to do.

33:38.450 --> 33:40.702
(DOOR CREAKS)

33:40.780 --> 33:42.213
(DOOR THUDS SHUT)

33:45.320 --> 33:47.242
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

33:49.990 --> 33:53.619
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

33:53.690 --> 33:56.022
We should go.

33:56.100 --> 33:58.625
(ENGINE STARTS)

34:03.640 --> 34:05.938
(WORLD UNDONE PLAYS)

34:06.010 --> 34:08.604
* You're waiting

34:11.950 --> 34:14.145
* For tenderness to come...

34:37.470 --> 34:40.132
* Crying for three days

34:42.580 --> 34:45.640
* Now your eyes
are red and tired

34:48.150 --> 34:51.517
* You can't sleep
for three days

34:54.090 --> 34:57.651
* Now you're waiting
for tenderness to come

35:00.230 --> 35:03.154
* You're waiting
for tenderness to come...

35:11.410 --> 35:14.208
I heard about Klepper.

35:14.280 --> 35:17.204
He must've heard
you were coming
and decided killing himself

35:17.280 --> 35:20.374
was better
than a life in prison.
(SIGHS)

35:20.450 --> 35:22.441
Is that
how you figure it?

35:22.520 --> 35:25.216
Not exactly, no.

35:25.290 --> 35:27.884
I, uh,
found Klepper's burner

35:27.950 --> 35:30.453
in the RV.

35:30.520 --> 35:32.750
That's the number_ forensics
pulled off it.

35:32.830 --> 35:35.822
And this is the number
that you gave me.

35:35.900 --> 35:38.323
So, the way I
"figure it,"

35:38.400 --> 35:40.618
is that you gave us
a fake number

35:40.700 --> 35:42.236
so that_
we'd run in Circles

35:42.300 --> 35:44.063
while you ran
a trace on the real one

35:44.140 --> 35:45.960
so that you could
get to Klepper first.

35:46.040 --> 35:48.508
See, first-thought theater
was that you were doing it

35:48.580 --> 35:50.502
for Reddington.
I mean, he's not around,

35:50.580 --> 35:53.208
so you're carrying
his water for him.

35:53.280 --> 35:54.770
But then I checked.

35:54.850 --> 35:56.841
Since he's been in Missouri,
he hasn't been allowed

35:56.920 --> 35:58.808
any calls in or out.

35:58.890 --> 36:01.188
I can explain.
He doesn't know anything
about this case, does he?

36:01.260 --> 36:02.989
This is your Blacklister,
not his.

36:03.060 --> 36:05.085
(QUIETLY)
It's a good explanation.

36:08.630 --> 36:12.566
I can't tell you now,
but I'll tell you some day.

36:12.630 --> 36:16.088
For now,
I just need you to trust me.

36:16.170 --> 36:18.832
Did you kill Klepper?

36:18.910 --> 36:20.332
No.

36:26.950 --> 36:29.976
But I did let him
kill himself.

36:30.050 --> 36:32.245
Why?
Because he convinced me

36:32.320 --> 36:34.686
the benefit
outweighed the cost.

36:34.760 --> 36:36.455
The same way I'm trying
to convince you

36:36.520 --> 36:38.454
not to tell Cooper
what I've done.

36:41.600 --> 36:45.969
(SCOFFS) Because the benefit
outweighs the cost.

36:46.030 --> 36:47.918
(SIGHS)

36:48.000 --> 36:49.729
(VOICE BREAKING)
I think so.

36:55.640 --> 36:58.404
That's a decision you're gonna
have to make for yourself.

36:58.480 --> 37:01.199
(VOCALIZING)

37:03.020 --> 37:06.717
(VOCALIZING)

37:06.790 --> 37:09.782
* Now you're waiting
for tenderness to come *

37:24.170 --> 37:25.569
Sir?

37:25.640 --> 37:27.062
Autopsy's in on Klepper.

37:27.140 --> 37:30.974
All indications are
it was a made.

37:31.040 --> 37:32.803
We found evidence
in Klepper's RV

37:32.880 --> 37:36.668
that'd he'd made these sort
of "ethical decisions" before.

37:36.750 --> 37:40.311
He killed 14 others.
That we know of.

37:40.390 --> 37:41.914
(SIGHS LIGHTLY)

37:41.990 --> 37:44.424
You seem...disappointed.

37:44.490 --> 37:45.923
Doesn't it bother you

37:45.990 --> 37:48.129
that's there's always
an ulterior motive?

37:48.190 --> 37:51.193
Some _reason we
were given a case
that's never fully explained?

37:52.330 --> 37:54.662
Not really, no.

37:54.740 --> 37:56.765
The way I look at it is,
because of us,

37:56.840 --> 37:58.364
a serial killer is dead.

37:58.440 --> 38:01.830
No one will ever suffer
because of him again.

38:01.910 --> 38:03.969
As far as I'm concerned,
the case is closed.

38:04.040 --> 38:08.511
Unless there's something
I'm missing.

38:08.580 --> 38:11.117
Is there?

38:11.180 --> 38:14.513
No, sir.
It's case closed.

38:17.720 --> 38:19.187
Marguerite Renard.

38:19.260 --> 38:20.818
The nurse.
We've got to find her.

38:20.890 --> 38:23.723
Before he found you,
could you have done it,

38:23.800 --> 38:25.165
what you did in the RV?

38:25.230 --> 38:26.663
LIZ:
She can't be hard to locate.

38:26.730 --> 38:29.563
And when we find her, we find
out who Reddington really is.

38:29.640 --> 38:31.289
Could you have done it?

38:33.570 --> 38:36.778
I don't think so. No.

38:36.840 --> 38:38.979
So he did this to you.

38:41.980 --> 38:44.983
What difference does it make?
We're so close.

38:46.881 --> 38:46.950
The difference that it makes
is that I'm worried

38:46.950 --> 38:48.815
that he's gonna do it to me.

38:50.090 --> 38:53.218
That won't happen.

38:53.290 --> 38:54.655
It won't.

38:57.960 --> 38:59.723
Okay.

38:59.800 --> 39:03.668
Marguerite Renard.
What do we know about her?

39:03.740 --> 39:06.231
Your friend, Mr. Rodrick.

39:06.310 --> 39:07.834
He's why you're here?

39:09.010 --> 39:10.705
Please tell me
you're gOIng to be

39:10.780 --> 39:12.839
administering
the Szondi test.

39:12.910 --> 39:16.710
I'm absolutely fascinated
by repressed impulses.

39:16.780 --> 39:19.283
There will be no more tests,
Mr. Reddington.

39:19.350 --> 39:20.840
Our work is finished here.

39:20.920 --> 39:23.115
That seems premature.

39:23.190 --> 39:25.226
I saw
all I needed to see today

39:25.290 --> 39:26.928
with your friend,
Mr. Rodrick.

39:26.990 --> 39:28.628
You keep calling him
my friend.

39:28.700 --> 39:30.224
He's not my friend.

39:30.300 --> 39:33.269
Well, whoever he is,
he was intent on killing me.

39:33.330 --> 39:36.834
I think he said
he was going to,
uh, "rip my tongue out."

39:37.740 --> 39:40.265
But your reaction
was everything.

39:40.340 --> 39:41.773
My reaction?

39:41.840 --> 39:44.035
You came to my defense.

39:44.110 --> 39:47.739
You saw that Mr. Rodrick
was intent on causmg me harm,

39:47.810 --> 39:49.448
and although
you don't know me,

39:49.520 --> 39:52.648
you made the very
conscious decision
to stop him,

39:52.720 --> 39:56.156
which, to my mind, is a...
is a wonderful demonstration

39:56.220 --> 39:59.986
of your ability to distinguish
between right and wrong.

40:00.060 --> 40:02.153
I'm not so sure of that.

40:02.230 --> 40:05.097
Yeah, but you're not
the doctor.

40:05.170 --> 40:09.061
Before I submit my decision,
I have one more question.

40:09.140 --> 40:11.290
I'm an open book.

40:11.370 --> 40:14.669
What exactly is it you want
from Mr. Rodrick?

40:17.310 --> 40:20.347
JUDGE WILKINS:
I have reviewed the results
of the psychiatric evaluation

40:20.410 --> 40:22.640
conducted
at the defendant's request,

40:22.720 --> 40:25.416
and it is Dr. Gray's
professional opinion that,

40:25.490 --> 40:27.981
while one with a criminal
history like Mr. Reddington

40:28.050 --> 40:29.915
would likely
have to be insane,

40:29.990 --> 40:32.481
it's clear his criminal
prOCIIVIties do not rise

40:32.560 --> 40:35.154
to the_ level
of legal insanity.

40:35.230 --> 40:38.028
It is the doctor's
profeSSional Opinion
that the defendant

40:38.100 --> 40:40.921
does understand
the charges leveled
against him

40:41.000 --> 40:43.639
and is, therefore,
fully mentally competent

40:43.700 --> 40:45.839
to assist in his own defense.

40:45.910 --> 40:47.764
Mr. Reddington,
you've been provided

40:47.840 --> 40:50.502
with a copy
of Dr. Gray's findings.

40:50.580 --> 40:53.208
Are you objecting
to her conclusions?

40:53.280 --> 40:54.838
No, Your Honor.

40:54.920 --> 40:57.844
I'm prepared to accept
the finding of competency.

40:57.920 --> 41:01.310
Wonderful.
Then we're clear to proceed.

41:01.390 --> 41:03.051
Mr. Sima?

41:03.120 --> 41:06.157
Your Honor, of the indictments
that are before the court,

41:06.230 --> 41:08.289
the prosecution
has elected to proceed

41:08.360 --> 41:10.021
with the charge of treason

41:10.100 --> 41:13.160
as our first case
against the defendant.
Very well.

41:13.230 --> 41:16.336
We'll move to jury selection
immediately.
(GAVEL BANGS)

41:16.400 --> 41:19.039
(DOOR CREAKING, THUDS SHUT)

41:19.110 --> 41:21.874
(KEYS JINGLE, LOCK ENGAGES)

41:21.940 --> 41:24.079
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

41:24.140 --> 41:25.539
(LOCK DISENGAGES)

41:25.610 --> 41:29.068
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

41:41.760 --> 41:43.159
(PLASTIC RIPS)

41:48.970 --> 41:50.392
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

41:50.470 --> 41:52.768
(LINE RINGING)

41:53.570 --> 41:56.778
(CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEPS)

41:56.840 --> 41:58.774
You got the phone.

41:58.850 --> 42:01.501
Yes, thank you,
and not a moment too soon.

42:01.580 --> 42:03.172
Why? What's wrong?

42:03.250 --> 42:05.343
I spoke
with Atticus Rodrick.

42:05.420 --> 42:07.047
Was he any help?

42:07.120 --> 42:09.281
He gave me a name...

42:09.360 --> 42:11.851
General Shiro.

42:11.930 --> 42:13.818
I need you to find out
everything you can about him.

42:13.890 --> 42:16.097
General Shiro?
Yes.

42:16.160 --> 42:18.924
He's the next name
on the Blacklist.
